**Overall Meaning:**

This verse describes the importance of water for sustaining life and emphasizes the consequences of neglecting hydration. It states:

"Dear one, a person is sixteen-parted.  For me, eighty nights, may I drink water! The breath, made of water, will be cut off if it does not drink."

The verse highlights the vital role of water in sustaining the body. It suggests that our bodies are composed of sixteen parts, each dependent on water for its function.  It also states that our vital force (prāṇa), which is made of water, cannot survive without proper hydration. 

The verse emphasizes the importance of respecting our bodies' needs and recognizing the essential role of water in our well-being. It warns against neglecting our hydration and emphasizes the consequences of dehydration. 


